  },
  "acceptance": [
    "new content AI results persist one immutable initial review revision atomically with result completion; legacy results remain explicitly unversioned until an authorized edit creates the first revision without fabricated history",
    "only existing super_admin or content_admin content-review actors may read or append revisions, and authorization happens before result or revision lookup",
    "PUT accepts only result public identity, expected revision/digest and a strict reviewed question or paper draft; it rejects client owner, task, source digest, adoption state, citation, Provider, prompt or internal identity fields",
    "append is optimistic-concurrency protected, monotonically versioned, immutable and idempotent only for an identical canonical draft digest; stale or conflicting edits fail closed",
    "canonical digest binds result public id, source content digest, target type, revision and complete normalized draft with bounded size and no raw Provider or secret data",
    "history and detail expose only the authorized structured review projection plus revision metadata; no cross-owner, organization, raw Prompt, Provider payload/error, internal id or unsafe citation detail leaks",
    "formal adoption requires and records the exact current server-owned review revision/digest, rejects stale browser commands and never consumes a client-supplied full draft",
    "review revision, adoption record, formal draft writer and audit remain fail closed on conflict; generated-knowledge confirmation and selected-mode adoption invariants remain GREEN",
    "migration is purely additive and legacy-safe with no default, backfill, UPDATE/DELETE, destructive DDL, apply or real database access",
    "F-0158 remains open_partitioned and F-0169 remains untouched"
  ],
